  "texts": [
    "Generally, the layers closer to the model output are more application-specific, and should be trainable to adapt to our application.",
    "In our experiment, let n be the number of trainable layers nearest to the model output, while the remaining layers are frozen.",
    "For example, n = 0 refers to the Base model where no layers is trainable.",
    "In A-Learn, we explore different settings of n ranging from 1 to 12.",
    "Due to the limit of space, we report the representative ones with the minimum n = 1 layer, about half of the layers with n = 7, and all the layers with n = 12.The results show an increase in accuracy as the number of trainable layers n increases, reaching a peak accuracy of 91.3% when all layers are trainable."
  ],
